  "prompt": "Do US presidents get bodyguard protection after they have left the office?",
  "response": "Yes, former U.S. presidents are entitled to receive security protection after leaving office. According to the Former Presidents Protection Act of 2012, former presidents are provided with Secret Service protection for the rest of their lives. This protection can also extend to their spouses and children under certain circumstances. However, this protection can be withdrawn under specific conditions, such as if a former president declines the protection or if their conduct is deemed a threat to security. Prior to the 2012 law, former presidents received protection for a limited period after leaving office.",
